# Audit Inventory — {{PROJECT_NAME}}

Canonical deduplicated list of every finding across every audit run. Per-run `findings.md` files are filtered **views** — do not add findings there, add them here.

**Last updated:** {{DATE}}
**Audit runs recorded:** 0

---

## How to read this file

| Column | Meaning |
|---|---|
| **ID** | Unique identifier. Format: `<CATEGORY>-<MODULE>-<N>` or `<PREFIX>-<N>`. See methodology for convention. |
| **Type** | `bug`, `gap`, `idea`, `risk`, `opportunity`, `regression` |
| **Module** | Area of the codebase (or `[SHARED]` for cross-module) |
| **Summary** | One-line description |
| **Status** | open · triaged · escalated · in-progress · closed · dropped |
| **Severity** | P0 (critical) · P1 (high) · P2 (medium) · P3 (low) |
| **First Seen** | YYYYMMDD — audit run that first recorded it |
| **Last Updated** | YYYYMMDD — most recent change to this row |
| **Audit Runs** | Comma-separated list of audit runs that confirmed this finding |
| **Escalated To** | Link to backlog entry, plan, or decision (when status is `escalated` or later) |

